==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*brestanan''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[bersta]], Old Saxon [[brestan]] (Dutch [[bersten]], [[barsten]]), Old High German [[brestan]], Old Norse [[bresta]].

